com.blukii.infosdk

Class InputElement

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.blukii.infosdk.InputElement
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    android.os.Parcelable

    public class InputElement
extends java.lang.Object
implements android.os.Parcelable
    Data object that defines the input data for resolving requests to blukii Info Manager (https://manager.blukiiinfo.com).

    It is used in two cases:
    • Callback BlukiiClient.OnDiscoveryListener.onDiscoveryResult(ArrayList):
      InputElement is part of every OutputElement. It contains input type InputSourceType.BLUKII and the device name of the discovered BLE module.
    • Function BlukiiClient.resolveInputElement(InputElement, BlukiiClient.OnResolveInputElementListener):
      InputElement is used as input property for a single resolving action. It has to be created by contructor InputElement(String, InputSourceType).
      If resolving is successful it will be unmodified part of OutputElement that is returned by Callback BlukiiClient.OnResolveInputElementListener.onResolveResult(OutputElement).
    See Also:
    OutputElement, InputSourceType, BlukiiClient.initDiscovery(BlukiiClient.OnDiscoveryListener), BlukiiClient.resolveInputElement(InputElement, BlukiiClient.OnResolveInputElementListener)

    • Constructor Detail

      • InputElement

        public InputElement(java.lang.String tagID,
            InputSourceType inputType)
        Constructor for creating an InputElement.

        The format of parameter tagID depends on the inputType.

        If an InputElement is part of a returned OutputElement property OutputElement.getId() return the tagId as conversion into a blukii number string.

        The following input types and formats are supported:
        • InputSourceType.BLUKII:
          tagId has to match a valid blukii number format: "blukii [B|S|K]XXXXX [6x hex-number] .
          E.g. "blukii BXXXXX 01234567890AB"

        • InputSourceType.NFC:
          tagId has to match a valid nfc id format: 14x hex-numbered string.
          E.g. "01234567890ABCD", will be converted to "TCXX01 234567890ABCD".

        • InputSourceType.SCAN:
          tagId has to match one of the following formats. If it is part of a returned OutputElement property OutputElement.getId() contains a convertes blukii number string
          • EAN-8: 8-numbered string, e.g. "12345678", will be converted to "blukii CHXXX8 XXXXX1234567"
          • EAN-13: 13-numbered string, e.g. "1234567890123", will be converted to "blukii CDXXX3 123456789012"
          • UPC-A: 12-numbered string, e.g. "123456789012", will be converted to "blukii CGXXX1 012345678901"
          • PZN-7: 7-numbered string with a leading "-", e.g. "-1234567", will be converted to "blukii CEXXX7 XXXXXX123456"
          • PZN-8: 8-numbered string with a leading "-", e.g. "-12345678", will be converted to "blukii CFXXX8 XXXXX1234567"
        Parameters:
        tagID - formatted input string, depends on inputType
        inputType - type of input id
        See Also:
        OutputElement, InputSourceType, BlukiiClient.initDiscovery(BlukiiClient.OnDiscoveryListener), BlukiiClient.resolveInputElement(InputElement, BlukiiClient.OnResolveInputElementListener)
